# DHCP on every wired Ethernet interface present at boot. Wildcard
# matches any name starting with "en" (modern systemd predictable
# interface naming: enp0s31f6, eno1, ens3, etc.) plus the legacy
# "eth*" naming some older kernels still produce.
#
# Live ISO ships ifupdown-style configuration for simplicity — Debian
# 12 still includes ifupdown by default and it's the path of least
# friction for "DHCP on whatever NIC is plugged in." NetworkManager
# would be heavier and brings a dbus dependency we don't otherwise
# need.

auto en*
iface en* inet dhcp

auto eth*
iface eth* inet dhcp
